oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Start-up of semi-continously operated and completely stirred dry fermentation pilot-scale biogas reactor
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Virkkunen, Elina
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Environmental aspects
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: In the year 2008, MTT Agrifood Research Finland built a pilot scale biogas reactor of 4.5 cubic meters situated in Sotkamo research station. The aim is to develop a completely stirred and semi-continuously operated biogas reactor that handles solid biomass.
oai_dc:dc.dc:identifier: Virkkunen, Elina (2009) Start-up of semi-continously operated and completely stirred dry fermentation pilot-scale biogas reactor. In: NJF Report, Vol 5, No 3, Nordic Association of Agricultural Scientists, p. 37.
